    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-09-05T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-09-05T17:00:00-05:00" n="654"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d654">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">884.6363 African Exploration and Development
                    Corp./29: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-09-05T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 5, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>53. Your 88, September 4, 8 p.m. You are authorized, in communicating the
                    Company’s decision to the Emperor, to include in appropriate language the
                    substance of paragraph 2 of your 88, September 4, 8 p.m., but modified to read
                    “helpful in the cause of peace” instead of “helpful to Ethiopia.”</p>
                <p>You should also bring to his attention the substance of my statement quoted in
                    the Department’s No. 51, September 3, 5 p.m.,<note n="98" xml:id="d654fn98">See
                        footnote 96, <ref target="#pg_781">p. 781</ref>.</note> and give particular
                    emphasis to the second paragraph of that statement referring to “the central
                    point in the policy of this Government.”</p>
                <p>I am confident that you will be able to convince the Emperor that my intervention
                    in the matter of the oil concession was motivated solely by a desire to preserve
                    the peace, to remove impediments to peace, and strengthen the hands of those
                    Powers, including the United States, which are making strenuous and sincere
                    efforts to that end.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
